Renderer context creation. We have to consider if using testImplementation helps discover Plexus component descriptors, which it does. I'll also check for the necessary versions of related modules.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"Doxia Site Renderer 2.0.0 is a standalone renderer around Doxia parser modules and Maven skin artifacts; several normal renderer paths need non-transitive/provided artifacts on the test classpath.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.maven:maven-artifact:3.6.3\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The 2.0.0 SiteRenderer API exposes org.apache.maven.artifact.Artifact for skin contexts, while doxia-site-renderer declares maven-artifact as provided because Maven normally supplies it.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.maven.doxia:doxia-module-apt:2.0.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The upstream 2.0.0 POM explicitly adds this parser module for tests because Doxia modules are no longer in doxia-core and their component descriptors must be on the classpath to render typical site documents.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.maven.doxia:doxia-module-xdoc:2.0.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The upstream 2.0.0 POM explicitly adds this parser module for tests because Doxia modules are no longer in doxia-core and their component descriptors must be on the classpath to render typical site documents.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.maven.doxia:doxia-module-fml:2.0.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The upstream 2.0.0 POM explicitly adds this parser module for tests because Doxia modules are no longer in doxia-core and their component descriptors must be on the classpath to render typical site documents.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No Docker image, external service, environment variable, or system property was found to be required. Generated tests should use the 2.0.0 API shape: RenderingContext was replaced by DocumentRenderingContext, SkinResourceLoader and enableLogging are gone, and meaningful rendering tests should create temporary local site/skin resources and obtain/inject DefaultSiteRenderer's Doxia, Velocity, ParserModuleManager, and Plexus collaborators rather than relying on old 1.9.1 helper methods.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The compile failure shown in the issue is primarily an API migration problem; these dependencies do not make the old 1.9.1 tests compile unchanged.\",\n    \"If tests use a Plexus/Sisu container pattern copied from upstream tests, additional test-only tooling such as plexus-testing may be convenient, but it is not required as deterministic setup because manual collaborator injection is possible.\",\n    \"Native Image and local Gradle verification remain authoritative for any further metadata needed by Velocity, Plexus, or Doxia parser discovery.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_08e7bdcfb0306606016a3faf00b12481968d668b5da7c0ad28\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 763, "output": 1547, "cacheRead": 37376, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 39686, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782558449755, "responseId": "resp_08e7bdcfb0306606016a3faef237548196a52e12d69bdedf7f"}}
